<item>
            <title>[SOLR-17745] Reduce leader election optimization never occurs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-17745</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It appears the optimization in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-14942&quot; title=&quot;Reduce leader election time on node shutdown&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-14942&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-14942&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; never actually happens. The reason is the seemingly innocuous check of &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/solr/blob/57de0e8dece2f333a624b6498d139af31d00038c/solr/core/src/java/org/apache/solr/cloud/ZkController.java#L2154&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;zkController.isClosed&lt;/a&gt; which actually ends up always skipping the leader election node cleanup. This is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; because the ZK session is actually closed but rather a side-effect of the complex implementation of &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/solr/blob/d1498e8d5a7f4382a83a2800a0d1568bcd0f2a55/solr/solrj-zookeeper/src/java/org/apache/solr/common/cloud/SolrZkClient.java#L852-L854&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;SolrZkClient::isClosed&lt;/a&gt; which also checks its &quot;higher level&quot; for closure. The higherLevelIsClosed delegates to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/solr/blob/6d84e8f97611685df7b39278737ca7bc9fc326d8/solr/core/src/java/org/apache/solr/cloud/ZkController.java#L355&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;CoreContainer::isShutDown&lt;/a&gt; which actually gets set to true in an &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/solr/blob/6d84e8f97611685df7b39278737ca7bc9fc326d8/solr/core/src/java/org/apache/solr/core/CoreContainer.java#L1299-L1308&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;earlier point in the shutdown sequence&lt;/a&gt;. Thus this optimization never materializes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A seemingly easy fix for this would be to check SolrZkClient::isConnected instead of isClosed. Will follow up with a PR.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
